properties.headline: Wind Chill Advisory issued January 16 at 5:15AM AKST until January 17 at 12:00PM AKST by NWS Juneau AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Very cold wind chills expected. Wind chills as low as
40 below zero.

* WHERE...Portions of the Haines Highway northwest of Haines.

* WHEN...From 8 PM this evening to noon AKST Friday.

* IMPACTS...The dangerously cold wind chills could cause frostbite
on exposed skin in as little as 10 minutes.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Temperatures have warmed Thursday morning
and therefore wind chills are not as dangerous today. However,
expect temperatures to fall again this evening, and wind chills
will once again become dangerously cold.
properties.instruction:
Use caution while traveling outside. Wear appropriate clothing, a
hat, and gloves.
